A the same time, a memo from an NYPD chief asked officers to avoid fanning rage within the ranks by limiting comments 'via all venues, including social media, to expressions of sorrow and condolence. ... Even in our most difficult times, we will remain consummate professionals.'

Brinsley traveled by bus to New York City on after wounding his girlfriend. Before the shootings, Brinsley wrote on an Instagram account: 'I'm putting wings on pigs today. 

They take 1 of ours, let's take 2 of theirs,' officials said. He used the hashtags Shootthepolice RIPErivGardner (sic) RIPMikeBrown - references to the police-involved deaths of Garner and Brown.

The slayings come at a tense time; Police in New York and nationwide are being criticized for their tactics, following the July death of Garner, who was stopped on suspicion of selling loose, untaxed cigarettes. 

Amateur video captured an officer wrapping his arm around Garner's neck and wrestling him to the ground. Garner was heard gasping, 'I can't breathe' before he lost consciousness and later died.

